 aws cloudformation validate-template --template-body file://cfm/website.yaml #validate your stack 

# create a stack

aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name s3websitestack --template-body file://cfm/website.yaml 

grab a path for your template from s3 bucket 

/cf-templates-zwjqxbha3f1h-us-west-2/202116421f-website.yaml 

aws cloudformation deploy --template-file /cf-templates-zwjqxbha3f1h-us-west-2/202116421f-website.yaml --stack-name news3website

create bucket 
upload a template

aws s3 cp cfm/website.yaml s3://cfmgsbucket/website.yaml 

deploy your stack 

aws cloudformation deploy --template-file cfm/website.yaml --stack-name s3websitestack --s3-bucket cfmgsbucket

updating a template after uploading index and error html files

makes index and error files public

get key of your objects

aws s3api list-objects --bucket www.gurlalsidhu.com

acl of your objects

 aws s3api put-object-acl --acl public-read --bucket www.gurlalsidhu.com --key error.html

get hostzoneid

aws route53 list-hosted-zones-by-name 